<subSubSection id="C3190BAFCD127B41FF13FB69FBACFAF5" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBC5824CD127B41FF13FB69FBACFAF5" blockId="11.[151,1437,764,1293]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">
<emphasis id="B9778436CD127B41FF13FB69FF43FB11" bold="true" box="[151,249,1233,1257]" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Remark:</emphasis>
These juveniles might belong to either 
<taxonomicName id="4C0323A7CD127B41FD08FB6AFCC2FB11" authority="Haddad, 2015" authorityName="Haddad" authorityYear="2015" box="[652,888,1232,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Diploglena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arida">
<emphasis id="B9778436CD127B41FD08FB6AFD59FB11" box="[652,739,1233,1257]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">D. arida</emphasis>
Haddad, 2015
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C0323A7CD127B41FC1EFB6AFB11FB11" authority="Haddad, 2015" authorityName="Haddad" authorityYear="2015" box="[922,1195,1232,1257]" class="Arachnida" family="Caponiidae" genus="Diploglena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="462" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karooica">
<emphasis id="B9778436CD127B41FC1EFB6AFBA9FB11" box="[922,1043,1233,1257]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">D. karooica</emphasis>
Haddad, 2015
</taxonomicName>
, both of which occur in the extreme north-western 
<collectingRegion id="49C796C6CD127B41FE23FB4CFD87FAF5" box="[423,573,1268,1293]" country="South Africa" name="Northern Cape" pageId="11" pageNumber="462">Northern Cape</collectingRegion>
in the vicinity of Port Nolloth (Haddad 2015).
</paragraph>
